Pretoria Police have opened an inquest docket after a police officer was found dead at a hotel in Arcadia on Tuesday. According to police spokesperson Captain Ndivhuwo Mulamu, the officer was in Pretoria from Easter Cape attending a police course. Mulamu refused to give the officer’s name but confirmed that they have opened an inquest docket. “At this stage, we cant say he was killed or he committed suicide, hence we have opened an inquest docket,” she said. Mulamu said their investigations will reveal what may have lead to his death. -TNA Reporter